SIMPLE: precious
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Precious
<hw>Pre"cious</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[OF.
<ets>precious</ets>, <ets>precius</ets>, <ets>precios</ets>, F.
<ets>pr⟦eacute⟧cieux</ets>, L. <ets>pretiosus</ets>, fr.
<ets>pretium</ets> price, worth, value. See <er>Price</er>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>Of great price; costly; <as>as, a <ex>precious</ex>
stone</as>.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧The <xex>precious</xex> bane.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Of great value or worth; very valuable; highly
esteemed; dear; beloved; <as>as, <ex>precious</ex>
recollections</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>She is more <qex>precious</qex> than rules.</q> <rj><qau>Prov.
iii. 15.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Many things which are most <qex>precious</qex> are neglected only
because the value of them lieth hid.</q> <rj><qau>Hooker.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>Also used ironically; as, a <xex>precious</xex>
rascal.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Particular; fastidious; overnice; overrefined. Cf.
<er>Pr⟦eacute⟧cieuse</er>, <er>Preciosity</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Lest that <qex>precious</qex> folk be with me wroth.</q>
<rj><qau>Chaucer.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Elaborate embroidery of <qex>precious</qex> language.</q>
<rj><qau>Saintsbury.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Precious metals</b></col>, <cd>the uncommon and highly
valuable metals, esp. gold and silver.</cd> -- <col><b>Precious
stones</b></col>, <cd>gems; jewels.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Preciously</ent>⟦br⟧
